  { :name => "RAV", :url => "http://rav.rubyforge.org/", :description => "Deprecation Warning. Unfortunately RAV hasn't been updated since the days of Rails 1.1. If you're looking for a way to visualize your Rails apps, you would do well to investigate Railroad, a more up-to-date project with similar goals." },
  { :name => "Conspire", :url => "http://rubyforge.org/projects/conspire/", :description => "Conspire is a real-time collaborative editing platform using Git as a transport layer." },
  { :name => "Augment", :url => "http://augment.rubyforge.org/", :description => "Augment is a system for gathering metadata from code and displaying it. This metadata will include test failures, test coverage levels, complexity metrics, and others. The display frontends are pluggable so as to interface with many editors and environments." },
  { :name => "Bus Scheme", :url => "http://bus-scheme.rubyforge.org/", :description => "Bus Scheme is a Scheme written in Ruby, but implemented on the bus! Every programmer must implement Scheme as a rite of passage; this is mine. Note that at least half of the implementation of Bus Scheme must be written while on a bus. Documentation, tests, and administrivia may be accomplished elsewhere, but the majority of actual implementation code is strictly bus-driven. Patches are welcome especially if they were written while riding a bus. (If your daily commute does not involve a bus but you want to submit a patch, we may be able to work something out regarding code written on trains, ferries, or perhaps even carpool lanes.) Bus Scheme is primarily a toy; using it for anything serious is (right now) ill-advised. Bus Scheme aims for general Scheme usefulness optimized for learning and fun. It‘s not targeting R5RS or anything like that." },
  { :name => "flay", :url => "http://rubyforge.org/projects/seattlerb", :description => "Flay analyzes ruby code for structural similarities. Differences in literal values, variable, class, method names, whitespace, programming style, braces vs do/end, etc are all ignored. Making this totally rad." },
